.TH HUSHWHEEL 1 "March 2026" "hushwheel 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hushwheel \- theatrical dictionary fixture with a giant static glossary table
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hushwheel
.I lookup TERM
.br
.B hushwheel
.I prefix PREFIX
.br
.B hushwheel
.I category NAME
.br
.B hushwheel
.I stats
.br
.B hushwheel
.I about
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Hushwheel Lexiconarium is a deliberately oversized but mechanically simple C program. It
stores a giant static table of whimsical civic terms and exposes direct lookup, prefix scans,
category scans, statistics, and archive notes.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B lookup TERM
Print the full glossary entry for TERM.
.TP
.B prefix PREFIX
Print every entry whose term starts with PREFIX.
.TP
.B category NAME
Print every entry filed under NAME.
.TP
.B stats
Print entry, category, district, and average ember-index counts.
.TP
.B about
Describe the archive in one short paragraph.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I src/hushwheel.c
Production source with the full glossary table.
.TP
.I include/hushwheel.h
Program data model and entry-point declaration.
.TP
.I docs/
Supporting documentation for concepts, testing, and packaging.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The program exits with status 0 on success, 1 on usage errors, 2 on missing command arguments,
and 3 when an exact lookup term cannot be found.
